@doorbedside
#end
:touch
#play tc
A door you know. Behind it, a lamp still burns,
and a shape is sleeping. Go back?
!west;Step back west, into the warm room.
!stay;No. Keep walking the hall.
:west
#play tfc
/w/w
#end
:stay
The door softens at its edges, and stays shut.
#zap touch
#end
:touch
Just the hall now. It has always been the hall.
#end
    end

    stat at 13,5 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF0 under Normal color 0x78
    oop
@doorlaugh
#end
:touch
#play te
You open it. Someone is laughing on the other
side, in a kitchen full of afternoon light.
You can almost see who.
#play tf
Then it is only a hallway again.
#zap touch
#end
:touch
A yellow door. You are sure something was here.
#end
    end

    stat at 29,20 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF0 under Normal color 0x78
    oop
@doorname
#end
:touch
#play tc
Behind this one, a voice is saying your name,
over and over, the way only they ever said it.
#play tcd
You lean close to listen -- and the sound thins
to nothing, like breath on a cold window.
#zap touch
#end
:touch
This door is warm. You cannot say why.
#end
    end

    stat at 53,11 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x18 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@signup
#end
:touch
#play tc
Scratched into the plaster, an arrow, and below
it a word that keeps sliding out of focus:
a phone... a booth... someone waiting to talk.
The corridor here has gone soft, unfinished.
Step into the pale seam to answer.
#end
    end

    stat at 53,14 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x19 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@signdown
#end
:touch
Same word, the same arrow. The hall repeats,
and you cannot tell if you are further along
or exactly where you began.
#end
    end

