  stats
    stat at 32,3 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x05 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@keeper
#end
:touch
#play tcefg
The garden-keeper is a smudge of green
where a woman used to stand.

She does not turn. She is watching a bed
of flowers gray to ash, one row at a time,
in the exact shape of your footprints.

:more
#zap touch
I planted these together with someone.
#play tc
I water them every dawn. It does no good.

The color keeps leaking west, toward the
door, toward the room where the lamp is
going cold.
#end

:touch
#zap more
She speaks without moving her ruined face.
#play tcf
The bright ones ahead are the last of it.
The gray behind you is what we've lost.

Walk east while there is still something
left to walk toward.
#end
    end

    stat at 32,21 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0F under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@bloom
#end
:touch
#play tcgec
A single flower still holds its color,
stubborn and impossibly bright.

You cannot say whose favorite it was.
Only that it was someone's, and that
knowing it once mattered more than air.
#end
    end

    stat at 59,11 element Passage cycle 0 p3 board "The Wall of Faces" under Empty color 0x00
    stat at 59,12 element Passage cycle 0 p3 board "The Wall of Faces" under Empty color 0x00
  end
end

