@f1
#end
:touch
#play tc
The features slide off this one like rain
down glass. A woman, maybe. Kind eyes, or
the memory of kind eyes. Not the face.
#end

    end
    stat at 14,6 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x02 under Normal color 0x08
    oop
@f2
#end
:touch
#play tc
A laughing mouth with no one attached to it.
You are almost certain you never knew this
laugh. Almost.
#end

    end
    stat at 22,6 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x01 under Normal color 0x08
    oop
@theone
#end
:touch
#play te-g
#give torch 1
This one you know. You know the way the
brow furrows before a joke, the small
crooked warmth of it. It steadies as you
look, the way a name steadies on the tongue.
You hold it. Hold it. Hold it.
#zap touch
#set found
#play tcegc
The portrait glows and grows still, at last
in focus. Behind you, something unbolts.
#send gate:open
#end
:touch
You have it now. Go, before it slips.
#end

    end
    stat at 30,6 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x02 under Normal color 0x08
    oop
@f4
#end
:touch
#play tc
A face made entirely of the color of a coat
you cannot place. Familiar as weather.
Wrong.
#end

    end
    stat at 38,6 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x01 under Normal color 0x08
    oop
@f5
#end
:touch
#play tc
Someone from a station platform, once. A
stranger you have grieved by mistake. The
grief was real. The face was not.
#end

    end
    stat at 46,6 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x02 under Normal color 0x08
    oop
@f6
#end
:touch
#play tc
This one has your own eyes in it, borrowed.
The dream runs low on faces and starts to
reuse the parts. Not the one.
#end

