    stat at 26,10 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x01 under Water color 0x18
    oop
@face
#end
:touch
#play tcdefg
There is a face on the water.
It is looking up at you the way you
remember it looking up at you.
/i
You lean closer to be sure of the eyes.
/i
The water shivers. The eyes come apart
into ripples, and the ripples into fog.
/i
You cannot say now whose face it was.
Only that it was loved.
#zap touch
#end

    end

    stat at 25,17 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xFA under Water color 0x18
    oop
@footprint
#end
:touch
Your own footprints trail out onto the
lake, dark on the pale water.
/i
As you watch, the nearest one fills
with fog and is gone. Then the next.
The lake is unmaking the path behind you.
#play s.c.-a
#zap touch
#end

    end

    stat at 32,21 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x0F under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@reflection
#end
:touch
Something pale drifts just under the
surface, keeping pace with you.
/i
A reflection with no one above it to cast
it. It raises a hand you do not raise.
/i
Then it thins, the way breath thins on
cold glass, and there is only the dark.
#play sc-c-c
#zap touch
#end

    end

    stat at 7,18 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF7 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@marker1
#end
:touch
A stone marker, wet and half-sunk.
The name carved on it has worn smooth.
#play tc
#zap touch
Now the marker is only a stone.
#end

    end

    stat at 18,18 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF7 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@marker2
#end
:touch
Another marker. You feel you should know
what it says. You feel it very strongly.
#play tc
#zap touch
The feeling passes, like all the rest.
#end

    end

    stat at 29,18 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF7 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@marker3
#end
:touch
The fog is thicker here. Sound goes flat.
Somewhere east the fog thins to a door.
#play tcg
#zap touch
The door is still east. It is all you
have left that is still true.
#end

    end

    stat at 41,18 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF7 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@marker4
#end
:touch
You touch the cold stone and try, hard,
to hold one thing about them in your mind.
/i
The color of a coat. A laugh. Anything.
/i
You hold it for a moment. Then it is
just fog on your fingers.
#play s.c.-c.-c
#zap touch
#end

    end

    stat at 51,18 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0xF7 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@marker5
#end
:touch
The last marker before the eastern shore.
It is blank. Perhaps it always was.
#play tcd
#zap touch
Cross the water east. There is a room
waiting that no longer knows your name.
#end

    end
  end
end

board "The Empty Room"
  max-shots 0
  dark false
  reenter false
  time-limit 0
  exits north none south none west "The Lake of Fog" east none

  start player at 1,12
  grid
